  log4j-core > They need a logging implementation, but also bridges of each of the major logging APIs to support log statements from the libraries they use. For example, your application might be logging against Log4j API and one of its dependencies against SLF4J. In this case, you need to install log4j-core and log4j-slf4j2-impl . To make things a little bit more tangible, consider the following visualization of a typical Log4j Core installation with bridges for an application: Figure 1. Visualization of a typical Log4j Core installation with SLF4J, JUL, and JPL bridges Requirements The Log4j 2 runt
